The paper proposes a method to improve uncertainty estimation in deep neural networks, which is a common problem in machine learning. The method involves generating challenging examples using an autoencoder-based generative model, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of soft labels and entropy, which are concepts commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for detecting out-of-distribution inputs, which is a topic commonly studied in computer security (cs.CR).
